		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "Human T-cell leukemia virus type 1 ( HTLV-1 ) is the etiologic agent of adult T-cell leukemia . <S>",
			"relation": "BACKGROUND"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "Tax , the viral protein , is thought to be crucial in the development of the disease ,",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "since it transforms healthy T cells in vitro",
			"relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "and induces tumors in transgenic animals . <S>",
			"relation": "COMPARISON"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "We examined the effect of Tax activity on the growth of the interleukin-2 ( IL-2 ) -dependent T-cell line CTLL-2 . <S>",
			"relation": "ROOT"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "Stable expression of Tax in CTLL-2 transformed cell growth from being IL-2 dependent to IL-2 independent . <S>",
			"relation": "FINDINGS"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "Tax stimulated transcription through NF-kappaB and the cyclic AMP-responsive element-like sequence in the HTLV-1 promoter . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "The finding of Tax mutants",
			"relation": "ADDITION"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "segregating these two pathways",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "suggested that the NF-kappaB pathway was essential for IL-2-independent growth of CTLL-2 cells",
			"relation": "SAME-UNIT"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "while the CRE pathway was unnecessary . <S>",
			"relation": "COMPARISON"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "However , both pathways were necessary for another transformation-related activity ( colony formation in soft agar ) of CTLL-2/Tax . <S>",
			"relation": "COMPARISON"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "Our results show that Tax has at least two distinct activities on T cells ,",
			"relation": "FINDINGS"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 13,
			"text": "and suggest that Tax plays a crucial role in IL-2-independent T-cell transformation",
			"relation": "ADDITION"
		},
		{
			"id": 15,
			"parent": 14,
			"text": "induced by HTLV-1 , in addition to its well-known IL-2-dependent cell transformation . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		}
	]
}